  <li id="comment-16115" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.ucsusa.org" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Karen</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/02/candy-is-dandy/#comment-16115"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-02-05T15:09:00-05:00">Thursday, February 5, 2009 at 3:09 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, sorry for all the disappointments, but at least we know the granola was good! I don&#8217;t think I&#8217;ve told you what I&#8217;ve been doing with that chocolate granola recipe of yours, so perhaps now is the time. </></>First, skip the coconut (mostly because I never have any in the house) and up the volume of oats and sliced almonds to compensate. Omit the sugar (we like it a bit less sweet) and throw in a little flax seed to boost the nutritional value. Then, instead of chocolate, I&#8217;ve been using an equal amount of those tart dried cherries from Trader Joe&#8217;s. Voila. Not chocolate granola anymore, but YUM anyway!!</p>
    </div>

